28/10/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police have arrested 12 persons suspected of backing al-Qaeda, local media reported on Wednesday (October 27th). 
The arrests were made in simultaneous operations in Istanbul and the city of Van. 
Weapons and bomb-making materials were seized. 
Several days ago, police arrested five people, including three students, for suspected links to al-Qaeda. 
(DPA, Anadolu news agency, Reuters - 27/10/10)
